The paper deals with interpreting the predictions made by LSTMs, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related tasks. The paper also discusses the ability of LSTMs to learn complex and non-linear relationships, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes an interpretation algorithm, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of LSTMs in computer vision tasks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the contributions of combinations of words or variables to the final prediction of an LSTM, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
